REALITY CHECK: TAKEN Seconds APART 👍🏽 It's been a little bit since I've done a reality check! 
For those of you that are new to my page welcome! 😍 
I like to show moments of reality to help keep things in perspective! 
Let's get to it:  ARMS 💪🏽 ➖➖➖➖➖➖➖➖➖➖➖➖➖➖➖➖
➡️➡️On the left: Everything relaxed, No posing ➡️➡️On the right: Stomach sucked in, left arm flexed and right arm posed ➖➖➖➖➖➖➖➖➖➖➖➖➖➖➖➖
For the longest time I got down upon myself for not having defined arms like I was seeing via social media. Especially in pictures taken of me! 
I still catch my self with this reality check. 
When I finally realized I was comparing my "normal" to flexed and posed pictures did I open my eyes to more self love. 
There is absolutely nothing wrong with any of these photos. 
They are all me. 
Taken seconds apart. 
But society has created a stigma that "flexed", "posed" and even photoshopped photos are superior. It's created a false sense of reality and unrealistic expectations that can cause discouragement! 
A simple reminder that our normal is reality and it can be created into a highlight reel too. 
So next time you find yourself comparing yourself, STOP. 
We are all uniquely made and have our own beautiful normal. 
We are all human, learning to embrace your struggles is a beautiful journey! It allows you to grow. 
Use social media for positive motivation and not negative! Our mindsets really are our reality! Live in a positive one 💕
